igion","header":"Reverted name spelling to ancestral Pierrepont","body":"Hezekiah Beers consciously restored the older spelling 'Pierrepont' to the family name, undoing the simplified 'Pierpont' his immediate American forebears had adopted. The change held in his Rochester branch — his son Jonathan Edwards Pierrepont and granddaughter Caroline Editha Pierrepont (later Ward) carry the Reverend's preferred spelling forward."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Would have inherited the lost English titles","body":"Per family tradition, when Hezekiah's older brother Evelyn died at sea off Norway in 1812 unmarried, Hezekiah became the head of the American branch — and would have inherited the disputed English Pierrepont titles and estates had the family's claim to them ever been recognized. The Pierrepont book treats this with appropriate skepticism."}],"slug":"hezekiah-pierpont-1792"},"H00814":{"id":"H00814","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"generation_from_thomas":6,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1795},"parents":{"father_id":"H00351","mother_id":"X00324"},"tags":["killed_in_duel"],"sources":[{"short":"Edward Hooker 1909","entry":"814"}],"death":{"year":1823},"gender":"male","marriages":[],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"James Pierpont","first_name":"James","last_name":"Pierpont","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"james-pierpont-1795"},"H00815":{"id":"H00815","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"generation_from_thomas":6,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott